  "text": "3.6 Torulene increase the expression of AR and PSA Downregulation of AR inhibits the proliferation of LNCaP cells. [CITATION_1] To investigate whether the induction of apoptosis by torulene was due to the downregulation of AR, cells were subjected to western blot and quantitative PCR analysis. As shown in Fig. 6 , torulene signicantly decreased AR and PSA protein and mRNA expression in a dose-dependent manner in LNCaP cells. Torulene treatment at 30 mmol L À1 for 24 h downregulated AR by 29%, whereas PSA was down-regulated by 28% compared with the control, respectively.",
